Merging Data Sets¶

creating an age group for the planes¶

In [8]:
def categorize_age(age):
    if pd.isnull(age):  # Handle NaN values
        return 'Unknown'
    elif age >= 20:
        return 'Old Aircraft'
    elif age >= 10:
        return 'Standard Aircraft'
    else:
        return 'New Aircraft'
In [9]:
Qn2B_list = []

for file in qn2b_list:
    # Merge each dataframe with 'manufacture'
    Qn2B = pd.merge(file, manufacture, on="TailNum", how="inner")
    
    # Calculate plane age
    Qn2B['PlaneAge'] = Qn2B['Year'] - Qn2B['Made']
    
    # Remove data with manufacturing year 0 or negative plane age
    Qn2B = Qn2B[(Qn2B['Made'] != 0) & (Qn2B['PlaneAge'] > 0)]
    Qn2B = Qn2B.dropna(subset=['PlaneAge', 'ArrDelay'])
    Qn2B['ArrDelay'] = Qn2B['ArrDelay'].astype(int)
    
    # Apply categorize_age function to create age groups
    Qn2B['AgeGroup'] = Qn2B['PlaneAge'].apply(categorize_age)
    
    Q1 = Qn2B['ArrDelay'].quantile(0.25)
    Q3 = Qn2B['ArrDelay'].quantile(0.75)
    # Calculate the interquartile range (IQR)
    IQR = Q3 - Q1
    # Define the lower and upper bounds to identify outlier
    lower_bound = Q1 - 1.5 * IQR
    upper_bound = Q3 + 1.5 * IQR
    # Filter out outliers
    Qn2B_wo_Outliers = Qn2B[(Qn2B['ArrDelay'] >= 0) & (Qn2B['ArrDelay'] <= upper_bound)]
    

    Qn2B_list.append(Qn2B_wo_Outliers)

...plot and regression line¶

In [15]:
for Qn2B in Qn2B_list:
    Qn2B['AgeGroup'] = pd.Categorical(Qn2B['AgeGroup'], categories=['New Aircraft', 'Standard Aircraft', 'Old Aircraft'], ordered=True)
    current_year = Qn2B['Year'].iloc[0]
    plt.figure(figsize=(10, 6))
    # Group boxplot by 'AgeGroup'
    Qn2B.boxplot(column='ArrDelay', by='AgeGroup', figsize=(10, 6))
    plt.title(f'Distribution of Arrival Delays by Age Group without Outliers-({current_year}) ')
    plt.xlabel('Age Group')
    plt.ylabel('Arrival Delay (minutes)')
    plt.xticks(rotation=0)
    plt.grid(True)
    plt.show()
